This is a pretty good desk for the price in that it is not all particle board. The metal frame makes it more sturdy and the design is simple and practical. This is a good desk for a student; there is room on the top for a laptop and space for writing as well. The moveable shelf makes storing books and binders possible and it was easy to assemble. I would recommend this desk for anyone looking for a basic desk that looks good without being too expensive.
Great sturdy desk! Really essential to the room!
Perfect peace for our teenage daughter's room. Easy to assemble and goes with any decor.

It worked perfectly in a small space. I bought a computer tray to attach for the keyboard and had lowes cut an acrylic top to fit to keep from scratching. We also bought an inexpensive lamp at target to match. I would love to add a drawer, but the shelves adjust to possibly adding a couple storage baskets. Total cost was $125 with the added accessories! It's perfect!
I've been using it for my college studies for a couple weeks now, and I love it. Easy to assemble, great little desk.
This desk provides a great workspace, and adds a stylish touch to any room. It won't turn any heads, but it gets the job done. Extremely easy set up as well, but be careful as it will scratch easily.

This is a nice smaller desk that was easy for me to assemble by myself, with sturdy parts and good finishing. It's not heritage furniture, but for RTA it's well made and I didn't think it was at all difficult to put together. Be sure not to tighten all the screws until the very end, because you'll need to have that little bit of play in there to get all the alignments correct. But it was easily done within an hour. I like it--it looks sharp and holds up my monitor and keyboard with at least 18 inches of work room to the side. The shelves on the left hold the computer tower and several other items.

This took 15 minutes to set up, and only that long because I was putting it together by myself in a small bedroom area. I bought this desk to be a writing desk, and especially because of the fact that it had steel legs. (I don't like messing around with screwing too many things into cardboard / pressboard. That being said, the top is pressboard, but the holes come with anchors, which are perfect. As for wear/stability, it's not rock solid, but I do have it tucked into a corner, so I don't expect it to be a big deal. When assembled, it's small enough to move by myself without a problem.
My son's room looks awesome with the desk. It holds his computer and printer with room to write on. Just purchased it so we will see if it holds up. The price was decent also.
Purchased for my sons room for homework. A little difficult to assemble. They could have had better instructions. Seems sturdy considering price. Son is enjoying for his laptop and to do homework.

I have my diecut machines on this desk and it is wonderful. Holds all that I need for my two machines and other items related to diecuting. All the pieces that you need to go with your diecut are right there. I have been using it a lot. Just need to watch weight as it is restricted to a lower limit but for what I need the desk for it works great.
This desk is great, easy assembly and very sturdy.

Totally worth the price. We had it put together for our 12 yr old son's room as a desk in his room for homework. We paired it with a bright red desk lamp and it's perfect for what he needs and looks amazing in his room.

I love this desk! I bought it to fit in a small space in my guest bedroom to give myself an extra study space. It was super easy to put together. I was able to put it together myself, without any help, in less than half an hour. It looks really cute and it fits nicely in the space. I also love the shelves! Who doesn't love extra storage space? If you are looking for something simple to go into a smaller space. Then this is perfect!
I am very pleased with this desk. It's not so large and goes well in my dining or living room. My 11 year old granddaughter put it together within an hour. It was a great buy!

Took about a half hour to put together. The desk is very sturdy, and a bit heavy. Good construction, but the table itself is made of particle board, I believe. I put a decorative tablecloth over it, and protective plastic that was cut down to cover the entire top. Looks great, offers protection from scratches, and matches my 13 year old's bedroom colors. She is very happy with this purchase , so am I. The desk is going to be used for doing homework once school starts up again. I bought the desk on sale for $49.99 last week, can't beat the price!
Sturdy, looks great, easy to assemble. Perfect, especially for the price!
Super easy to put together. Looks great and functions as a great computer deak.
I love this desk. It was easy to put together, but only one hole was not lined up. The desk is taller usual. It fits a storage bin and long enough to hold up to 2 monitors. Great buy
Easy and quick to put together for my son and I. Sturdy but not heavy. Hope it does well over time.
I wanted a small desk to use as a sewing table. This desk perfectly fits the order :-)

I really needed this desk ASAP and when i was about to built it I saw i didnt receive any screws at all!!!! I live an hour and a half away from Target!!!!! Emailed the company about the missing screws and will hopefully receive them in the mail ( hopefully soon :/ )
instructions were the best easy to put togeather

I am quite surprised by how inexpensive this desk was and how sturdy and strong it holds up (so far). The structure is made of steel and so it's pretty rigid which is very important, and the wood table top is thick and free of nicks. The only thing on my wishlist for this item was that the mfg drilled holes to make the shelf reversible. You could try to drill your own holes if you wanted though, but it would have been nice to have both options.
This desk is easy to put together, it has a thick tabletop, and it's good for limited space.
Exactually what we were looking for my sons bedroom

This is a great basic desk that meets my exact needs. Something for my laptop and to hold some storage bins. Feels very solid, nice wood and metal. I was able to put it together myself (34 year old female), with little trouble. It looks very nice, and got a great deal!
It is a good size and easy to put together
very easy to put together. Nice looking and well built.
Real simple instructions . Very simple overall look very sleek and keeps from the typical paperwork pile up

This was pretty easy to put together, and goes well with my other furniture. It's not going to get used that much, so I'm not as concerned about the quality. If I was going to use it everyday I probably would have purchased a more expensive desk.
Very nice desk for the money. Wasn't sure if it would look cheap. It does NOT look cheap. Great for small places. Good shelf storage.
Took about 15 min to assemble, looks nice. Very basic, minimalistic. Light weight but pretty sturdy.
This desk was super easy to assemble and looks great!
Easy to set up took about 10 minutes. Seems durable. modern desk

This is a great desk for the price I paid. It is strong, attractive, and perfectly sized for what I needed. I was able to pick it up at my local target for free and they had it ready within a couple of hours of submitting my order. The desk was easy to assemble, feels well made and strong, and it has exceeded my expectations.

This was a great purchase. Took me about an hour to assemble and discretely sits in a corner of my living room. I was a little hesitant because of the price and thought the quality might suck but it works.
It was easy to put together and seemed very sturdy. Could not beat the price and you got good quality for that price.

review_header: Aside from 1 faulty screw this was a great buy!
review_content: Very easy and simple assembly! Took me no time at all to assemble. Only issue was one screw would not go completely in however it did not compromise the stability of the desk overall. Only sometimes do I feel it gets a little shaky but as long as you don't do any aggressive moments it will be fine. It was a good buy in my opinion. I have my computer and monitor set up and adjusted the shelf to the topmost level to just hold my controller for when I game. I am very happy with this buy!

review_header: Nice desk for a great price
review_content: This desk is great. It is just the right size I needed it to be, is very sturdy and good quality. It may be made out of particle board but it is very thick and sturdy. The instructions where clear, easily understood and it was easy to construct. I would recommend this desk to anyone who is looking for a valuable desk that doesn't lack in quality and looks like it is worth more than what was paid.
I have used this desk for about 5 months now. It was well worth the $69 I paid for it. The desk is very sturdy and I use it in my home office. So go ahead and buy one you won't be disappointed.
Set up was a breeze. Great for kids room!
Desk is great quality. Simple, elegant,
This desk is exactly what I needed. It wasn't to expensive, nor did it look cheap for the price. It is cheap in price but expensive in design!
It was better than what I was expecting based on the picture from the site!
Great look! Easy assembly. Sturdy.

This is my first desk that ive ever bought and its the best. I do wish that they gave you another plank of wood for the storage area on the side of the desk but otherwise this desk is durable. The wood feels like its real wood, im not sure if it is or not but the wood will last awhile, I guarantee you that. Its the perfect desk for an small area, if you have children or teens I will recommend it for the value. And it only took me 30mins to put it together.

review_header: Can't beat it for the price!
review_content: Bought this on sale for $55 and its great!! Assembly was super easy. All individual pieces were labeled for what piece goes where. So simple. Solid. Fits well in a small room.

My old desk got some scratches on it from moving so decided to finally get a new one and i couldn't be happier about it. This desk is very study and solid. Set up was a breeze only took me about 15 minutes. The top shelf (of the two) is adjustable, you can put it at any bar level you want. Great amount of counter space, nice and long, not so much wide, and also quick side note, even though you cannot tell because the color matches perfectly, the legs are all metal. A great buy overall .
Bought this desk for our son and works great!!

review_header: I love this desk because its very sturdy & has a great style
review_content: Its perfect! Such a simple, yet beautiful desk. & very easy to assemble. I am one satisfied shopper (:
The desk works great for what I need it for!
Needed a small desk for my home office, just to pay bills and check laptop. This fits the needs. Took about 25 minutes to assemble, but overall a good value.
It's a little smaller than I thought, but I don't need a huge working space. Seems like sturdy construction as long as you don't abuse it. Put everything together in about 15 minutes

Easy to put together. Perfect size for the space in my bedroom and love it's open design. It's a clean and modern look. Suggest that the manufacturer provide an option to purhase a slide out tray for a laptop or keyboard that can be installed to underside of desk top. When there is a space constraint this is the perfect desk.
Easy installation. Great size.

I was looking for something simple, that looked decent, was sturdy, inexpensive and easy to assemble and this desk fit all my needs. I think it took me about 15 minutes to put it together and I must say, I am impressed. It holds my keyboard, mouse and mouse pad, monitor, speakers, (cpu tower and paper tray on the two shelves). The laminate top and shelves look nice. I got much more than I expected for a mere $69 bucks.

I purchased this product because it has such a high weight holding capacity, due to the metal frame. I was looking for something to hold my dart frog vivariums, which are very heavy. My only complaint is that the there are only two shelves (including the bottom) and that they are open. Storage space is more usable when enclosed so things don't need to look so neat. But for the money, it was a great purchase!

review_header: Does the job, and does it well
review_content: The desk does what it needs to do, does it well, and looks decent good doing it. Assembly was easy. All you'll need is a screwdriver. The manual is quite thorough and all the parts clearly marked. I like the black coloring. Matches my computer and accessories. Style is simple, nothing spectacular there, but function was more important to me. Has enough space on top to hold a decent sized monitor, speakers, keyboard, mouse, and a few other smaller things (quite spacious!), but still small enough to fit in the space I needed it to (my room is tiny, so a definite plus!) The adjustable shelf is great. I keep my computer tower on the lower (non-adjustable) rung, and the adjustable one is set to the highest setting, where I keep my external HDs and other small computer accessories. Since the shelf is open, my computer gets plenty of airflow to keep it cool, and raised just high enough to help avoid dust and pet hair from the carpet. If I had one nitpick, it's that it isn't QUITE big enough for a full tower computer (either on the top or the shelf), but mine's fine even with a couple of inches hanging over, so it's whatever. Quality-wise, it seems pretty solid. Top is thick, although it can scratch easily so be careful there. The steel supports are light but sturdy. I have zero worries of it bending from any of the weight on it. It'll wobble a bit if pushed on, but you have to really shake it to get anything to fall over. The only con I can even think of is the fact that it's a bit high for my computer chair, but I can't fault the desk for me and my chair being a bit too short. Just something to take into consideration though. Overall, if you're looking for a simple, functional desk at a decent price, this is a good bet.
Looks good, does the job, inexpensive, adjustable shelves, super easy to put together. Highly recommend if you're not worried about high quality furniture!
Looks very nice when all put together. The wood portion doesn't feel super cheap. It was easy to put together. I am please.

This piece shouldn't be anywhere where you'll nick the veneer because it's just particle board and it scratches so easily. However, the metal frame is sturdy and so are the shelves and tabletop, it's the perfect fit for my bedroom and so far it's doing its job perfectly, especially at under $70.
This was a gift for my 10 yr old son and its very good for the price. Easy to assemble. I was able to put it together on my own. Very sturdy and clean finish.
